review_blob: One of my favorite beers. As far as saisons go, this beer nails. Pours golden yellow with a slight cloudiness to it. Incredible floral and fruit scents. The taste is crisp and smooth.
Great beer. Very dark when poured. Strong wine esq grape nose. The flavor is complex with grapes, rich porter flavor, and a smooth wine barrel finish.
Great session beer. Has a nice smooth malt taste with a light crisp finish leaving only a slight lingering taste of yeast which is pleasant.

Spectacular beer. Better than most Tripels in my opinion. The nose is wheaty with slight hints of citrus. The front taste is wheat filled with a hint of sugar. The finish has a strong presence of the sugar used to brew this style.
Incredible beer. Very crisp and front heavy on the taste. The notes are of fruit and spice.
